quran[3]{c,v,t,f}:
  2,55,"And (remember) when you said: "
  2,56,"Then We raised you up after your death, so that you might be grateful."
  2,57,"And We shaded you with clouds and sent down on you Al-Manna {1} and the quails, (saying): ",footnotes:1:{2:57} Mujâhid said, "Al-Manna is a kind of sweet gum, and As-Salwâ, a kind of bird (i.e. quails)"...Narrated Sa‘îd Ibn Zaid رضي الله عنه: Allâh’s Messenger صلى الله عليه وسلم said, "The Kam’a (truffle i.e. a kind of edible fungus) is like the Manna (as it is obtained without any effort) and its water is a (medicine) cure for eye trouble." (Sahih Al-Bukhâri, Vol.6, Hadîth No.5). (S.B. 1714)